# Save Reading

Bookmark something for later, with enough context to find it again.

## Workflow

1. {{USER_PREFERRED_NAME}} drops a URL or asks to save context.
2. Fetch the page, extract: title, author, source, ~3-line summary.
3. Append to `state/reading_list.md` under `## To read`:
   ```
   - [ ] **Title** — Author / Source — captured YYYY-MM-DD
     [link](URL)
     <3-line summary>
   ```
4. Confirm with one line.

## Reading list shape

`state/reading_list.md`:

```markdown
# Reading List

## To read
<unread items, newest first>

## Read
<dated subsections of items {{USER_PREFERRED_NAME}} marked done>
```

## Marking done

When {{USER_PREFERRED_NAME}} says "I read X" or marks `[x]`, move from `## To read` → `## Read` under today's date.

## Optional integrations

- If a Notion DB is configured for reading (asked during anson Stage D), also create a row there.
- If `pocket-cli` or `instapaper` is installed, mirror to that service.

## State

`state/reading_list.md` — markdown, append-only.
